reviews.review_text: My friend and I came on a Sat at 11am and got in right away. When we left around noon, there was a bit of a line outside--something to keep in mind. Highly recommend the brioche French toast. Its crispy on the outside and soft on the inside. The French omelette was perfectly cooked but there was a bit too much dill inside for my taste. It comes with fries but I enjoyed it with sourdough instead and made little egg sandwiches :)

Excellent service, nice heated patio seatings for colder weather and most importantly, pet friendly! My friend and I visited with our pets, a cat and a small dog. We had the most pleasant experience at the restaurant with our furry friends  Thank you for letting us dine in! We will recommend to everyone and will come back again!

BEST EGGS BENEDICT EVER! I wasnt planning on bookmarking my very first stop in Vancouver to come back, but this place is one is not to miss!  We got off the cruise ship with luggage in tow and were warmly received, and bags were stored while we had a delightful brunch.   Quite the experience. Thanks everyone!

My favourite place for brunch in Metro Vancouver! The food was amazing and the menu isn t your average brunch menu. Staff were attentive and hospitable. The Egg Cocotte had perfectly poached eggs and the tomatoes, olive, red pepper sauce underneath was a burst of flavour. The French Omelette, again, was perfectly cooked and the herb and cheese inside paired well and was not too heavy. I don t really like fries but I kept eating their fries. Every piece was crispy and even after it cooled, they didn t become soggy. The Maxine s Bacon were thick cut bacon with a slightly sweet taste. They also have regular bacon as an add on if you prefer savoury bacon. They don t take reservations for brunch and their peak hours are around 11am to 1:30pm. If you re a party of 2, you ll be seated relatively quickly. Larger groups will be a longer wait as most of their tables seat 2-4 people. They also don t have an indoor waiting area so I wouldn t recommend coming on a rainy day if you don t want to wait in the rain.
We loved having brunch here. Meals were spectacular   fresh OJ, and cute atmosphere. Wonderful service by Anton
Super cute vibes !! Love a breakfast / brunch here . Super sweet staff and nice atmosphere. Yummy Dutch baby pancake   Emma, smash burgers are pretty bomb. I love all the coffee moments they have.

We went in without reservation on a Saturday around noon and were able to be seated without issue. Our waitress was so nice and attentive - my drink was not empty once! We ordered the salmon benny and it was so good, even the side salad was so flavorful and the hashbrowns were perfect, they were crispy on the outside but soft on the inside.

Hands down one of the best experiences Ive ever had. The staff were amazing, and I mean all staff. They were attentive and so knowledgeable of the menu. Drinks were topped up at all times, and the food was just epic. The venue was beautiful and even though we like to go to a different place everyday, we are going to come back to this spot for the next 2 days as we want to try as much as we can on this menu. We love a restaurant thats this efficient, this attentive and this perfect. Everything about it put it on my top 5 list of best breakfast restaurants of all time.
Egg Cocotte is my favorite, the crispy potato is super crunchy , even their Latte and London Fog were outstanding as well. Food

Went during the weekend early morning with no line for 2 people. Ordered French toast and the Dutch baby. Both taste delicious. I personally like the toast better with not too sweet berry sauce and mascarpone cheese perfectly match. Friendly service and nice decor in the store. Recommend

Friends and I went here in Summer 2022 and this place is just WOW. The French Toast is amazing, and I now make a trip here whenever I m in Vancouver. Highly recommend. (Sorry ate all the toast in the second pic)

Absolutely amazing restaurant. I love the atmosphere, food, and the pricing. Though not cheap, the pricing is fairly reasonable. We had the full Harwood, which consisted of an amazing roasted bone marrow dish, topped with eggs, sausage, bacon, roasted tomatoes, and bread. It was delicious. We were visiting from out of town and this was a major highlight of our trip. Well done! Will recommend to everyone!!

I came for a group birthday brunch and had a great time. The staff were friendly and efficient. Food was delicious and the portion sizes were good. We had fresh warm buttery croissants, beef brisket, eggs cocotte, eclairs, and French toast. The deserts were not overly sweet which was perfect for my preference.
Great first experience! Especially the service. Attentive and professional. Love the decor. Feels like authentic euro cafe. Great coffee.

Shared the Smoked Salmon Rosti with a friend and it was delicious! Wish I had ordered a second! Came back two years later for a birthday brunch and finally got to enjoy a full meal. The salmon eggs Benedict was DELISH. I have celiac and a dairy intolerance and they made all the adjustments they needed to accommodate me for which I am very grateful. My boyfriend got the West End Breakfast and really enjoyed it, he found it quite filling as well.
So tasty!, everything we order was delicious!, definitely we ll be back!, it s a good option for breakfast or Sunday brunch! Wheelchair accessibility: No stairs, and great indoor and patio space

Coffee 5/5 Had the iced mocha and latte, really nice flavours clearly high quality coffee Food 4.5/5 French toast and smoked salmon rosti, both beautifully plated and treated great. Might be an Asian andy take but was a bit sweet for my taste and would have liked the option for a side of fresh fruits. Service 5/5 No complaints, our server was professional and attentive

If you haven t dined at Maxine s, you re truly missing a special treat. The food is outstanding. For Sunday brunch, we had Blood Orange Mimosas and  The Full Harwood  ($65 for two), including roasted bone marrow, scrambled eggs, Maxines bacon, smoked brisket, sausages, tomato, baguette, crispy potato. It was out of this world! But the best part is the service! Our server today was Lydia and we ve had Javi in the past. The day manager was Maria. They are all super friendly and knowledgeable. They clearly love their work and it transforms the dining experience into a social delight :) And to top it all off, they are dog friendly. So, these three little ones don t have to be left behind.

This place deserves the hype/high rating. Can confirm the food was really good and the service even better. We had brunch here and the food quality and quantity were excellent. Initially I was wary of the higher price range for an average brunch but it was well worth it. The OJ was actually freshly squeezed, and even the basics like the house baked goods and fries were delicious. 10/10 would return.
Great little French Cafe. I got the Eggs Cocotte, which has a tomato base you can dip the grilled bread into- delicious.

DELICIOUS. ELEGANT. OUTSTANDING. In our week spent in Vancouver we had brunch at Maxine s twice and both were great experiences. I got the smoked brisket hash and my friends got the Dutch Baby and all of us shared amazingly fresh oysters! Ended the meal with a chai latte and it was so smooth and rich! Some might say that the hash brown is too much but I love having more grains to go with my food since I eat a lot of food with rice, the hash brown complimented the meal so much! Thank you to our server for being so helpful in your recommendations and having patience as well! Can t wait to go back next time!

My eyes were bigger than my stomach but Maxine s was sooo good. Came here once for happy hour but had to come back for an entree, was happy we did. Alona was an amazing server and she made sure we were taken care of and enjoyed our food at the highest level.

We had weekend brunch there, very busy place, but services is very efficient and very helpful, it is very hard to have professional service in Vancouver dining scenes, this place is exceptionally good. Coffee is very good, very well balanced and full body. I ordered smoke brisket on harsh, very creative use crispy harsh as bed, the porches eggs are perfection, very generously brisket on top, it is full package, it is restaurant supposed to be, to be treated and serviced, job well done. Thanks.

Definitely worth a visit!! Peak time for a Saturday brunch and the wait time was a mere 20 minutes (on a heated and sheltered patio). Servers were attentive and by no means did we feel rushed. The spot was busy but not overcrowded. The food was DELICIOUS. I want to go back and try everything on the menu! You won t be disappointed.

Literally one of the most amazing brunch experiences I ve ever had. Maria (the manager) was incredibly kind and energetic as soon as we walked in the door and Nicole (our server) was so lovely and attentive; the service in this place is unbeatable and I felt so happy to be there because of it. The atmosphere was also beautiful. The restaurant was so aesthetic and not too overwhelming visually, yet still well decorated. Great place to take family and friends who are visiting. :) The food was scrumptious! I had a eggs Bennie and genuinely one of the best bennies of my life  I m still thinking about it. I never write google reviews but this place deserves the best one yet. Maxine s is definitely my new favourite restaurant here in Van!!

Everyone was happy, the portions seemed small, but everyone was full by the end. The best bang for your buck is probably the Dutch baby though. We got the French toast to share and it was delicious, I love when French toast doesn t need the syrup to be perfect. If you want to get seated fast make sure you get here before 10:30, if you show up around 11, you will be in a fairly sized line up.

This place has had a lot of local buzz recently, so Ive been excited to see what all the fuss is about. After experiencing a sunny Sunday morning brunch here, I definitely understand why so many people love this place. We came in at 10AM, with a party of 3 and were seated right away. As time went along, it got really busy and the line built around the corner by 11AM. The interior is designed with a modern French Cafe vibe, while the service is highly professional and exceptionally friendly. We ordered the salmon rosti, dutch baby and french toast to share. The rosti and dutch baby are quite unique, delicious and beautiful dishes! The salmon rosti though, seemed to be our tables favorite. Unlike other places, we didnt leave feeling like the food was too heavy or greasy. The portion sizes are big, especially in comparison to other french restaurants in the area. We paired our food order with their iced lattes (definitely a must try, and can order them with either real milk or oat milk). Overall, Id say that Maxines represents the pinnacle of Vancouver brunch and I would highly recommend this place to visit with your best friends.

I loved it here. The vibes and the food! We ordered the dutch baby and the rosti. The dutch baby was so soft and and custardy. I was worried it would taste eggy but it did not. Perfect balance of sweet and salty. The rosti was also delicious. The potato base was a large crispy hashbrown with smoked salmon and dill cream (fav). I think ordering these for one person would be too much but i shared with my partner and it was the perfect amount for us. It was nice to take a bite alternating from dish to dish.

Very cute place! The brunch line wasn t long at all. All the staff were very nice and we even had 2 waitresses who were very attentive. We got the steak and eggs, two lattes and the west end. All were delicious! The jam was amazing and would come back just for that. The aesthetic of the place is very on point.

Came here for brunch and really love the vibe, service and food. Surprisingly they were busy but the line was not long for brunch at 11am on a sunny Saturday but we did sit at the bar. I really liked the Dutch Baby and the Salmon Rosti was good as well. However, I feel that the French Toast was a bit thick.

I absolutely adored the decor and style of this place, with all the glass windows and the plants. The food was phenomenal as well, especially the hash brown. Everything was so yummy and the dishes complimented each other very well. I would definitely recommend the freshly squeezed orange juice, it s honestly amazing.

We spied this adorable French Bistro as we were headed over the Burrard Street Bridge. The patio led us back there for a very delicious, very French Brunch. The flat white coffee was a treat as was the Eggs Benedict. Great service too! Well be back.
Service was great, food was amazing. The hash browns with the Benedict was great! Nice and crispy.

I drive by this place ALL the time and there is always a line up. I finally made the time to go around 10:30am and while there was a wait at the front, it went by super quickly (10-15 minutes wait which was reasonable unlike cafe medina s). Parking can be tough but if you drive further down near Burrard Place building there is street parking there (some free, some $2/hour). Hostess and servers were very nice and sweet. I sat outside in their patio which was super nice on such a sunny Vancouver day. When I wanted coffee to start, server showed me the boozy ones in case I wanted to try and I ended up ordering The Dudeness dalgona boozy coffee and it was pretty amazing!! Creamy and rich with just a bit (shot?) of alcohol; very yummy and high recommended!! Caesar was also tasty and came with a pickled green asparagus only. For food, one Google review mentioned the Dutch Baby being the  best value  so I ordered it without even knowing what a Dutch Baby actually is lol. So it comes in a skillet and it s almost a soft pudding-bread with ham, cheese and runny egg on top. It was pretty substantial and I couldn t finish it. Very tasty and the server offered to bring hot sauce, salt and pepper too. Also ordered an avocado sandwich and that was tasty; the avocado mash was mixed with something making it way more delicious than when I try the same at home lol. Overall the brunch was amazing and the lineup was always present and moving steadily (I watched while eating). There is also a side/back patio that s totally in the shade in case the front patio spots are too bright and sunny. Such a lovely brunch experience that I will definitely be back to try their other drinks which were the highlight and food (their french toast looked amazing too although seemed quite small).
Excellent service and beautiful place, I loved the vibe. The food is ok but no wow!. I guess it depends what you get...

Awesome food and service in a very comfortable setting. From the perfectly poached eggs, to the crisp hash browns, each dish was assembled with care.  Fresh ingredients, with a touch of salt.  The right cooking temperature, with the right amount of cooking time.  So simple, yet complex and difficult to pull off.  Cant remember the last time I really enjoyed brunch.  The awsome drip coffee tied everything together with the decor and ambience of the place.  Will come back for brunch again!

Had brunch here with a friend and really loved it. Firstly the ambience is great (warm lighting is great for photos!), so very instagrammable. The service was also great, our servers were always checking in on us and super friendly! I had the oat milk latte and the Dutch baby. Both were fantastic! Coffee was great and the Dutch baby was so delish! Its really a heavy meal so get ready to eat a lot of carbs. My friend had the cocktail, juice and the breakfast sandwich which she said was also very good. Very generous portions for sure! The only downside is that the space is not really wheelchair accessible, toilets too. Overall, we had a great time and I can totally see why this place is always crowded! Will definitely return!
Absolute gem. The brunch and vibe were amazing! Cant wait to go again

When you visit this place, be sure to try the amaretto sour, an outstanding drink. Youll be delighted to know that their pet-friendly terrace offers excellent service. Also, dont miss the opportunity to savor their delicious cuisine.

I m in love with this restaurant. European atmosphere with delicious brunch menu. We ordered Dutch baby, carbonara and salmon potato Rosti. Those dishes amazed us!! My personally favourite is Dutch baby. It brought me back to my favourite Dutch restaurant in Amsterdam. The price is reasonable, and I will definitely go back to try their dinner menu.

This place is delish! The food is really great, service was excellent and they have a really awesome list of gluten free options, meaning I could basically eat everything on the menu which is so rare. We went for brunch and everyone enjoyed their meals. Looking forward to coming back through

This is such a cute spot, we came for brunch on a rainy day and it was so Christmassy and cosy! The Dutch Baby was heavenly, pretty much a giant breakfast yorkshire pudding and the portion size is huge! The back bacon benny was also fantastic, and the rosties were nice and crispy. Can t wait to get back here and try the dinner menu! The server was great, very friendly and made great recommendations.
Great place and great food! European vibe and good location, brunch go-to! Tried a Dutch baby and salmon rosti together with foamy mimosas, truly amazing!

Cozy atmosphere, kind staffs and wonderful taste! Portion was perfect as well. I understand why ppl said Maxine is the best brunch place in the town. We tried Brioche french toast and Dutch baby and it was a perfect combination of savoury and sweet.  Ill be back for sure to try something else next time!

Just such a wonderful beautiful lovely place with kind people working here! They let my friend use the bathroom no questions asked. The Chicken! The macaroni! The mushroom thingy! The fries! (Some call them frites ) I just am so happy and have so much faith in the people and the world. Thank u!
Incredibly friendly staff, excellent food, many gluten-free options, festive atmosphere, outdoor dining available,  we found a Vancouver gem
Food was really good. We got the avocado alfalfa breakfast sandwich, dutch baby, and smoked salmon rosti. Everyone was happy with their dish and we ll definitely be back!

I ve eaten a lot of good food in my life, but nothing like the salmon potato rosti   literally the best thing I ve ever eaten. My mom and I had such a lovely meal and drinks here on my 30th birthday. The front of house staff (manger?) was welcoming and offered us a choice of seating. I can t wait to come back :)

Best to go early otherwise the lines starts to form after 10:30. This was a cozy place for brunch and the salmon rosti we had was so delicious. The potato was the highlight of the dish and although the portion may look small, it is extremely filling. We couldn t finish the whole dish as we were stuffed. Could do with less of the dill cream cheese and they really don t hold back. Would come back and try other dishes.

I may be bias as I used to work here, but honestly it is some of the best food, service, and atmosphere in Vancouver. It s especially perfect for someone with Celiac disease like me, as most things on the brunch menu can be made completely gluten free! They really employ the best people here all around and are doing everything right. I miss being able to eat here almost every day but anytime I visit Vancouver a Maxine s visit will be a top priority! Dietary restrictions: Celiac friendly

Perfect place to have a brunch in Vancouver. Tasteful cocktails and chill atmosphere are guaranteed. Thanks a lot to the waitress Alyona for excellent service. She made our evening wonderful. I definitely recommend this place.

We ate here twice while on vacation. Everything we ordered was incredible. I always order Eggs Benedict when I see it on the menu. Maxines is up there with the best Ive had.  Charming and friendly staff. Highly recommend you check it out.

Maxines is a restaurant in Vancouver that has great vibes and a really cool atmosphere. Parking around here can be tough so be ready to walk a bit. Staff are extremely friendly and helpful with choosing your meal. The food is delicious, lots of flavor and decent portion sizes although the prices are pretty high. But you pay for the experience and the service on top of just the food. This spot is great for date nights especially. Its got a few dozen tables inside, some outside and a bar area as well. Id recommend making reservations as they get pretty busy, especially around the weekend. Beets and burrata is pretty solid, and their steak is cooked wonderfully. Kid friendly as well which is always a plus.

This was our first stop after landing in Vancouver, and I dont have enough positive words for this place. Clair (apologies if the spelling is incorrect) was an amazing server/barista and made our time there welcomed. The food there was amazing and the Harwood Coffee was just chefs kiss. Had nothing like this and my wife who is not a coffee drinker, really loved this drink. Although pricier than most places, I believe its definitely worth the money. If I could give this restaurant a 6/5, I would.
Cool venue for a date night or a girls/boys night! Great cocktails   food was amazing. You have to try sun-chokes (had to Google that one). Service is also top notch. Highly recommend this place.

Really stylish room & great brunch menu. I recommend the breakfast sandwich - though veryone at the table was satisfied with their meal and great service  Looking forward to trying happy hour and dinner menus.
Light-filled brunch spot with heated patio. Great cocktails and rich, well crafted, brunch classics. Excellent, warm service.

This place is truly one of my favorites. I have been for both brunch and dinner and cant say Ive ordered anything I didnt like (food and drinks included). The service is great, I love the ambiance  and they take reservations (huge bonus).

Ricotta gnocchi with meatball and steak were cooked to perfection as were the sides. Large selection of wines. Service was excellent. We are in Vancouver for a week and have already made new reservations for our last night here!

My family and I are visiting Vancouver for a trip and decided to try out Maxines cafe & bar for breakfast. We showed up 10 min before opening time and they were able to accommodate us. The decor was very nice and they had comfortable seating. Perfect for a family. We had their Egg Cocotte and the Smoked Salmon Rosti. Both dishes were very good.  The Egg Cocotte was very flavorful and the egg was cooked perfectly. The tomatoes went very well with the egg and cheese. The Smoked Salmon Rosti was amazing. Although the ingredients seem heavy, it did not feel heavy at all. It was seasoned perfectly and the egg and Rosti was cooked perfectly as well. Oh, their cappuccino and latte were great as well. Hope to return to try their lunch and dinner menu some time.

The options for breakfast are limited, but the ones that is in the menu are perfect. I enjoyed my food. The french toast has a great look and presentation, but its not as perfect as you expect. Great atmosphere, welcoming service, delicious food.
Stopped for a few drinks and a quick snack during happy hour. Chickpea falafel was tasty and fresh and the drinks were delicious. Service was quick. Definitely want to come back for brunch some time.

Delectable new neighbourhood go-to spot! Currently there are a dozen small tables on the front sidewalk patio for outdoor dining, with a covered patio out the side currently awaiting completion. The interior is cheery, with classic ambience infused with modern touches. Staff go above and beyond. Though the menu doesn t state it, almost everything can be done gluten-free! (Can t wait to go through the whole menu.) The West End breakfast plate was tasty and filling. The latte was slightly on the bitter side for my taste, but the giant portion of spongy coffee cake balanced that out for me. Welcome to the West End, Maxine s!
My family and I had a wonderful experience at Maxine s. Both the food and server were five stars, and the ambiance was lovely. We had the la cocotte and the smoked brisket hash for brunch

Amazing brunch spot! Might be my new fav in Vancouver. Cant wait to try their dinner too. First pic is a crab benny but with roti I think its call (giant hashbrown) rather than the standard English muffin. Covered in Berranaise, side dollops of dill cream cheese, fresh dill and capers. Second is a mushroom and onion tart with poached egg and not sure about the cream sauce but was SO good! And a little cheese never hurt nobody, unless your lactose intolerant ;) Both were specials that day. Always get those while ya can.

The cutest cafe! The staffs are so friendly and they have a dog friendly patio (THANK YOU!!) had a short time here just having coffee and croissant today with my dog but will be back with humans for sure. - did go back!
Went for brunch on a Friday, was easy to get a table for a group of 6. Food and service was amazing. Everyone enjoyed their meal no complaints. Patio is spacious and heated.

I came here with my cousin and they were super accommodating with making sure we got a comfortable table since my cousin is pregnant and about to pop! Our server was super cute was nice. Unfortunately I dont remember her name but she told us she is in nursing school :) Gave us some super helpful tips with the menu. I chose the dutch baby which was delicious. It is definitely a combination of savoury and sweet. I loved the melted beschamel cheese that they poured on top. I would give this a try if you havent already! My cousin had the hash with the hollandaise on the side since shes pregnant. I ended up eating the hollandaise myself because it was so good lol. It was mixed with dijon and super tasty. The meat that came with the hash was also so good and had the right amount of fat mixed with meat. The bottom hash layer was perfectly cripsy and not too oily. I enjoyed the food here and the ambience and would love to come back and try more on the menu!

Great spot for weekend brunch, but it gets very busy after 10am on weekends, be prepared to wait for 20-30 mins. The food is great, especially the skillet dishes as well as the fried chicken sandwiches.

absolutely delightful. good sense of urgency to get us in and seated swiftly. sunday brunch culinary bliss; beef and hash with poached eggs and saurkraut + brioche french toast with whipped mascarpone and walnuts. fresh grapefruit juice.

Great brunch place, can be a bit busy on weekends during brunch hours, but the wait is not too long as they have plenty of space. We tried smoked salmon on a giant hashbrown (rosti) and dutch baby, both were delicious. Another time we tried the avocado breakfast sandwich that was nice but the one with bacon is better.

Urban setting, kinda French feeling, beautifully tree-lined & heated patio area, inside is inviting also.  Lots of variety on the menu from fresh oysters to burgers (changed-up for keto); Nice setting for a comfy casual social get together, frendly efficient service, good vibe!
One of the best places for brunch in Vancouver. The food is sooo good, and the vibe and ambience are also nice. It gets very crowded so best to reserve a table online in advance

Such a neat place with great food. Beware.. the parking situation is TERRIBLE. It took me 30 mins of circling around to find somewhere to park. You should definitely check this place out though and I can t take away a star for that. I had the Dutch baby and it was so delicious! I would definitely order that again. I love that it was a little out of the norm for a brunch item. Staff were really nice.

New fave brunch spot in town!  We gorged ourselves on Dutch babies and an amazing cocktail spread. Hands down the crispiest potatoes (rostis) to ever exist. I dare you to find a crispier potato!  Line up moves crazy fast too; unheard of in Van.

Absolutely delicious!! We got the French Toast (pictured here after several bites) and the Smoked Salmon Benedict - both outstanding with perfect portions. Maxines has a cozy atmosphere, safe outdoor dining, warm heat lamps, and friendly servers. Would highly recommend and we will definitely be back!

Our server Maria was amazing, she was bubbly and knowledgeable. We ordered the mussels and fries, kale salad and the steak tartare. Everything was amazing and hit the spot for us. We ll definitely be back again!

It could be casual or formal depending on what your mood is. Maxines is equally flexible to suit your plans. Great vibe, busy on the evenings, good food, nice people, great location.  Parking - good luck
The smoked brisket hash with sunny side up eggs was delicious, and very heavy! Service & latte were great as well. Good job guys!
Came for dinner. Had the Steelhead with beets. It was fantastic. The cocktails (gin sour and blackberry margarita were excellent too.
Nice place for brunch, food is delicious, the servers are friendly.

We had brunch here as a family of 10 and I have to say it was the best customer service we have ever received at a restaurant. The staff is lovely and our server Nicole W was impeccable. Her patience and kindness was one of a kind and it really made our experience special. The food was also 10/10.

Really loving Maxines for its location, service and food...and awesome coffees. This is the place to go for lunch with friends, business meetings, and just for drinks and food...pretty much everything. I love it love it love it. The patio is heated and awesome.

Delicious food and a great atmosphere. Will definitely be back :) The service was attentive, friendly and pro-active. Shoutout to Carol for her kindness! I am looking forward to returning soon when the speciality coffees hit the menu. Pro tip: arrive early on weekends to avoid waiting in line.
Cute little brunch place. Recommend getting there early on weekends as it gets busy.
Had great service and food, really need to go early for brunch as it fills up quickly, loved the French toast
Really cute must-try brunch place! The food is very filling and tasty. Service is great and I love the atmosphere and decor. They have lots of sitting inside and outside.

There is a description of Maxine s as honouring the European approach to create a neighbourhood restaurant and we concur in this fact..we arrived for dinner and felt a positive vibe immediately..the staff were welcoming and very friendly, the food was delicious and I personally appreciated the fries as one of the photos demonstrates  we will be back to this delightful restaurant
The food is absolutely delicious. Our server was lovely, knowledgeable and really eager to give great service (which she did). We will return very soon. Highly recommend it!
I love their patio, especially when it is sunny. The food is fine, and our server Natalie was very friendly and loving. I will visit again for lunch/brunch.
Delicious food , staff are very accommodating and attentive

Great place for HH! The place is laid out like a French bistro, with different rooms and a covered patio.  Two of us came in for a weekend happy hour and were pretty pleased with our tab. Bottles of wine $30, and a selection of beer and cocktails. We each had an appetizer (mine was the fried chicken, crispy sweet and hot!) and a large burger that came with fries or a salad at $15. I would definitely come in again to try their other appies on the hh menu.
Great food and atmosphere! Anthony was very helpful and knew exactly the right thing for me to order based on my preferences. Great experience and will definitely be coming back!
Maxines is the perfect place for a nice brunch, delicious food and great service in a beautiful little and cozy restaurant. Looking forward to going back!
Delicious French cuisine, lovely atmosphere and friendly service. I always love stopping by whenever I am in Vancouver, especially for their eclair!
Had brunch here and it was amazing, the lady jaye was so refreshing. The staff was so friendly and kind to us, I definitely can t wait to visit again. Thank you for the great experience!
Great place for brunch. The skillet its amazing .
I loved the place! Went there for brunch and the food was great!
The smoked salmon rosti was genuinely one of the best meals Ive had in months. Great service and a killer 80s soundtrack on the speakers. Just a great time all around
I had a wonderful breakfast and a truly gourmet cup of coffee, and very much enjoyed the company of the server at the bar, would recommend to anyone!
